This paper deals with the semantics of non-monotonic negation in probabilistic deductive databases, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of artificial intelligence (AI) and databases (DB). Therefore, cs.AI and cs.DB are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also introduces the notion of stable formula functions, which is related to logic (LO) and programming languages (PL), making cs.LO and cs.PL likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper deals with default reasoning, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning (LG), making cs.LG a possible sub-category.
